# Verify on Local Dashboard Only

For **this repository**, verification and acceptance testing target the **local CDR dashboard** served by **`cdr_dashboard_server.py`**, not the public AustralianRates production site.

## Rule

- **Default verify:** `npm run verify:local -- --base-url=http://127.0.0.1:<port>/` using the URL/port printed when the server starts.
- **UI / regressions:** Use **Browser MCP** (`user-browser_agent_cursor`) against that same base URL when requested (console, network, screenshots).
- **Do not** treat www.australianrates.com.au as the sign-off environment for AR-local changes; production Pages/Workers deploy is out of scope here.
- The dashboard still **reuses** AustralianRates **`site`** CSS/JS from disk when available; fixing styling may require a correct **`site`** checkout or **`--site-root`**.

## Rationale

AR-local ships as a **local Python server + static dashboard**. The real deploy pipeline on AustralianRates does not apply; verifying on the running local server is the honest acceptance path.
